// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`agh-design skill rules block (PR-1, task_03; PR-2, task_17) > Snapshot lock — rules block (task_17 subtask 17.9) > Should match the rules-block snapshot (locks future drift) 1`] = `
"**Rules that matter most for this brand (full reasoning in \`DESIGN.md\`):**

- **Dark mode only.** \`color-scheme: dark\` is hardcoded. Never render on a white background.
- **One accent: \`#E8572A\`** (\`--accent\`). Use sparingly — one accent target per viewport.
- **Warm-tinted neutral ramp**, never cool/bluish. Surface ramp: \`--rail\` \`#0c0b0b\` → \`--canvas\` \`#131211\` → \`--canvas-soft\` \`#1a1918\` → \`--canvas-tint\` \`#1c1b1a\` → \`--elevated\` \`#232220\`.
- **Translucent hairlines, not solid borders.** Use \`--line\`, \`--line-soft\`, \`--line-strong\` (rgba whites). The legacy solid \`#3C3A39\` divider is gone.
- **Two-token shadow vocabulary (ADR-003).** Only \`--shadow-overlay\` (modals) and \`--highlight\` (active rim) carry shadow. Cards, popovers, dropdowns, sticky headers, list rows stay flat with a 1 px ring on \`--line-soft\`. No drop shadows on content, no glassmorphism, no decorative texture.
- **Type stack:** Inter Variable for UI, JetBrains Mono for metadata + mono uppercase eyebrows (\`--tracking-mono\` = \`0.06em\`). Playfair Display reserved for \`packages/site/\` marketing hero only. NuixyberNext reserved for the \`agh\` wordmark only.
- **Eyebrow primitive is mandatory for every uppercase mono label.** Render through \`<Eyebrow>\` (\`@agh/ui\`) with \`case="upper"\`, \`size\` (\`eyebrow\` default = 11 px / \`badge\` = 10 px / \`micro\` = 9 px), and \`tone\` (\`muted\` default / \`subtle\` / \`strong\` / signal palette). Inlining \`font-mono\` + \`uppercase\` + arbitrary \`text-[Npx]\` / \`tracking-[Nem]\` values is forbidden — see \`DESIGN.md\` §3 and the \`tokens.css\` \`--text-eyebrow\` / \`--text-badge\` / \`--text-micro\` / \`--tracking-mono\` contract.
- **Signal colors are desaturated and tint-only.** Success \`#5fbf85\`, warning \`#d6a647\`, danger \`#e0635a\`, info \`#8e8eb5\`. Appear as low-alpha tints on chips/pills, never as solid banners.
- **No emoji. No bluish gradients. No colored-left-border cards** (except the one highlighted row in the comparison table).
- **Copy is operator-first and dry-confident** — engineer-to-engineer, no hype, no "we", no exclamation marks. See \`COPY.md\` for the full product-language spec.
- **Surface glaze tokens are mandatory.** Use \`--row-hover\`, \`--row-selected\`, \`--surface-glaze\`, \`--bar-fill\`, \`--input-fill\`, \`--btn-default-fill\`, \`--btn-default-hover\`, \`--badge-fill\`. Inline \`bg-[rgba(255,255,255,…)]\` literals are forbidden — see ADR-001 §6.
- **Owner / kind palettes route through \`--avatar-{agent|human|system}-{0..N}-{bg,fg}\` tokens.** Raw owner hex literals under \`web/src/**\` and \`packages/ui/src/**\` are forbidden — see ADR-001 §7.
- **Modal-scrim alpha is \`0.55\` and applies \`var(--overlay-blur)\` (3 px).** \`backdrop-filter: blur(...)\` is permitted only on \`.dialog-scrim\` / \`.sheet-scrim\`; every other surface stays blur-free — see ADR-001 §2 and \`DESIGN.md\` §10.
- **\`::selection\` resolves to \`var(--accent-tint)\` (10 %).** \`--overlay-selection\` is deleted; do not reintroduce it — see ADR-001 §1.
- **Shadow vocabulary is two tokens only — \`--shadow-overlay\` (modals) and \`--highlight\` (active rim).** Inventing \`--shadow-card\` / \`--shadow-pop\` is forbidden — see ADR-001 §4 and \`DESIGN.md\` §6.
- **\`--neutral-tint\` is pinned at \`rgba(150, 150, 155, 0.06)\`.** Drifting to cooler \`(122, 122, 128, …)\` channels is forbidden — see ADR-001 §8.
- **\`--font-display\` is an Inter alias reserved for \`tokens.css\` and explicit logo/wordmark slots.** Production code under \`web/src/**\` and \`packages/ui/src/**\` must not consume \`var(--font-display)\` for type-ramp purposes — see ADR-001 §5 and ADR-002 §12.
- **Tailwind \`rounded-md\` / \`rounded-lg\` / \`rounded-xl\` utilities are forbidden.** Resolve every radius through the token contract — \`rounded-(--radius-xs)\` / \`rounded-(--radius)\` / \`rounded-(--radius-md)\` / \`rounded-(--radius-lg)\` / \`rounded-(--radius-icon-well)\` — see ADR-001 §9 and \`DESIGN.md\` §14.
- **Inlining \`font-mono uppercase tracking-mono\` (or arbitrary \`tracking-[Nem]\`) tuples for label purposes is forbidden.** That combination IS the eyebrow contract; render through \`<Eyebrow>\` instead — see ADR-002 §1 and \`DESIGN.md\` §3.
- **Body baseline is pinned to Inter 13.5 px / line-height 1.5 / letter-spacing −0.006em / \`font-feature-settings: "cv01", "ss03", "cv11"\`.** Set once in the \`tokens.css\` body rule; never override per-page — see ADR-002 §6 and §9.
- **Mono identifiers in row contexts (task-row, kanban-card, inbox-item, run-row) render as bare mono text, never as \`<Pill mono>\`.** See ADR-002 §1 and \`analysis.md\` §5.2.
- **Lucide icons use \`strokeWidth={1.75}\` by default; only at the 11 px \`xs\` size does \`strokeWidth={2}\` apply.** The size ramp is 11 / 12 / 14 / 16 px (\`xs\` / \`sm\` / \`default\` / \`lg\`); the unifying \`<Icon>\` helper lands in PR-2 (task_10) — see ADR-010 §9.
- **\`Loader2\` from \`lucide-react\` is banned in production routes (\`web/src/**\`).** Use \`<Spinner>\` for "this surface is loading data" and \`.dot--pulse\` for "this entity is in an active running state" — see ADR-009 §5 and ADR-010 §8.
- **Shell grid is \`56 px rail + 244 px sidebar + 1 fr content\`.** Sidebar collapses to 220 px at viewport ≤ 1100 px and to a drawer overlay at ≤ 880 px via \`useSidebarViewport()\` (returns \`"default" | "md" | "drawer"\`). Never inline panel widths or breakpoint literals — see ADR-003 §4 and ADR-005 §1.
- **Active workspace nub + selected nav rail + selected list-row rail all paint \`var(--fg-strong)\`** (white, 2 × 16 px). Accent stays reserved for the active CTA, the rail logo plate, and the active rail brand identity — never the active row, never the active tab indicator — see ADR-003 §3 and DESIGN.md §11 "Accent overload".
- **\`<Topbar>\` is the canonical route-identity surface.** Use the slot vocabulary \`{ title, trailing, count, back, backLabel, meta, overflow }\` per ADR-005 §8; the count chip flows automatically from \`useNavCounts()\` when the route declares \`topbar: { navCountKey: "tasks" | "jobs" | … }\`. \`@agh/ui\` MUST NOT call \`useNavCounts()\` directly inside \`<Topbar>\` — \`useTopbarShellModel()\` resolves the count and passes it as a prop — see ADR-005 §3.
- **Detail-mode topbar swaps to \`back + title + id-chip + sep + meta + spacer + actions + overflow\`.** The back slot is a 20 × 20 ghost chevron; back behaviour resolves through \`router.history.back()\` with parent-route fallback. Detail surfaces emit \`<DetailHeader>\` (24 px H1, 6-row anatomy) in addition to the topbar swap — see ADR-005 §5 and ADR-003 §2.
- **\`<RuntimeConnectionIndicator>\` is the single owner of the daemon LED.** No rail-bottom LED, no per-row LEDs. The footer dot encodes \`connected + degraded\` via the tone-and-pulse rule (\`success\` solid / \`success\` pulse / \`danger\` solid). The degraded heuristic flips when ANY \`useNavCounts()\` entry carries \`stale: true\` — see ADR-005 §1.
- **\`<Button>\` runtime variants are additive: \`default | primary | outline | secondary | ghost | destructive | success | link | neutral\` (9 total).** \`primary\` is an initial-parity alias for \`default\` (accent CTA); \`neutral\` paints \`var(--btn-default-fill)\` → \`hover:var(--btn-default-hover)\`. Border-color hover is banned everywhere; \`<Button variant="outline">\` is reserved for legacy callsites and forbidden in new code — see ADR-004 §1 and DESIGN.md §10 "Don't trigger accent on hover".
- **\`<Pill>\` ships 4 px radius across every size (\`xs\` / \`sm\` / \`md\` → 17 / 19 / 22 px height).** Neutral pill is borderless tint-only. Mono variants emit \`font-semibold tracking-[0]\` 10.5 px regardless of size. The \`uppercase\` prop is gone — callers that need uppercase emit \`className="uppercase"\` themselves or compose \`<Eyebrow>\` — see ADR-004 §3 and ADR-002 §1.
- **\`<PillGroup>\` track is borderless \`var(--canvas-soft)\` + \`var(--radius-md)\` (8 px), 2 px padding, 1 px gap.** Segments render Inter sentence-case 12 px / 510 / -0.005em (never \`font-mono uppercase\`); active state lifts via \`var(--elevated)\` + \`box-shadow: var(--highlight)\`. Count badge is 3 px radius literal on \`var(--badge-fill)\` / \`var(--muted)\` with \`tabular-nums\` — never \`var(--accent)\` — see ADR-004 §4.
- **\`<Tabs variant="line">\` underline is \`var(--fg-strong)\` 1.5 px (NOT \`var(--accent)\` 2 px).** Active count chip is \`bg-[rgba(255,255,255,0.07)]\` / \`var(--fg)\` — never accent. \`<Tabs variant="lane">\` ships the \`·\`-separated lane-tab pattern with bare mono 10.5 px / \`var(--faint)\` counts (no chip wrapper). The chipped \`variant="default"\` is deprecated — see ADR-003 §7 and ADR-004 §2.
- **\`<Empty>\` icon-well is borderless \`var(--canvas-soft)\` / \`var(--radius-lg)\` (10 px).** Layout is top-padded (64 / 0 / 0), not flex-centered. Title 18 / 510 / -0.022em via \`--text-empty-h1\`. Description max-width 54ch. CTA \`margin-top: 22 px\` — see ADR-004 §6.
- **\`<Metric>\` and \`<KpiCard>\` are flat (no border).** Labels are sentence-case Inter (NOT uppercase eyebrow); metric value 22 px via \`--text-metric-value\`, KPI value 28 px via \`--text-kpi-value\`. \`<KpiCard>\` is the canonical export — \`<DashboardCard>\` was hard-renamed in PR-2 with no alias — see ADR-004 §9 and DESIGN.md §11 "Eyebrow misuse".
- **\`<Dialog>\` title is 13.5 px / 510 / -0.012em via \`--text-modal-title\`.** Header padding 13/18, footer 11/18 on \`var(--canvas-soft)\`, body 18 px. Close button 26 × 26 ghost. Scrim resolves \`var(--overlay-scrim)\` (0.55) + \`var(--overlay-blur)\` (3 px). Modal width ladder is \`--modal-w-sm / --md / --lg\` (560 / 720 / 880 px) — never inline \`sm:max-w-*\` — see ADR-008 §1 and ADR-011 T-1.
- **\`<RadioCard>\` selected state paints \`var(--surface-glaze)\` + \`box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--line-strong)\`.** Never \`border-(--accent)\` or \`bg-(--accent-tint)\`. Padding \`9 / 11\`, radius \`var(--radius)\` (6 px). Hover state lifts to \`var(--elevated)\` — see ADR-004 §8.
- **\`<CatalogCard>\` is flat, padding 16 px, hover \`var(--elevated)\`.** Logo well is 24 × 24 (default) or 40 × 40 (\`logoSize="lg"\`) with \`var(--surface-glaze)\` background, \`var(--muted)\` glyph. Selected state is inset \`var(--line-strong)\` ring + \`var(--surface-glaze)\` — never accent border, never accent tint — see ADR-004 §7 and ADR-011 §8.
- **Form inputs ship \`bg-(--input-fill)\` + transparent ring at rest** (12.5 px / -0.005em, 8/11 padding, 32 px height). Focus paints \`bg-(--canvas)\` + \`box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--line-strong)\`. \`<Textarea variant="mono">\` opts into 12 px JetBrains Mono. Inputs MUST NOT override height through \`h-9\` / \`h-10\` inside form modals — see ADR-008 §9 and analysis.md §4.
- **Use \`<DetailHeader>\` for the detail hero — never inline a 24 px H1.** The primitive renders the 6-row anatomy (crumbs / pre-title / 24 px H1 via \`--text-detail-h1\` / pills / meta / actions); \`back?: () => void\` mounts the 20 × 20 ghost chevron. The 22 px page-head tier is gone from the runtime; \`<Section>\` H2 is 13 px and never a page-level H1 — see ADR-003 §2 and DESIGN.md §11 "Section as page-head".
- **Use \`<FormSection>\` (not \`<Section>\`) inside modals and editable forms.** Container is \`var(--canvas-soft)\` / \`var(--radius-lg)\` / 18-20 padding, no border. Head is 13 / 510 / -0.008em via \`--text-section-head\`; optional leading icon + right-aligned eyebrow slot. Row gap 6 px, between-row spacing 14 px. Form-row hints sit inline with the label, never below the input — see ADR-008 §9 and ADR-015 §7.
- **Use \`<MonoId>\` for identifiers in row contexts** (task-row, kanban-card, inbox-item, run-row, breadcrumbs, agent IDs, run IDs). The primitive renders bare lowercased mono 10.5 px via \`--text-mono-id\` / \`--tracking-mono-id\` (0) with optional inline copy slot — pass the raw identifier, the primitive lowercases at render time. Identifier \`<Pill mono>\` is banned — see ADR-002 §1 and ADR-014 §3.
- **Use \`<RunCard>\` for active-run + standalone run-detail rendering.** Top row pill stack (status pill + \`<MonoId>\` run-id + session info + attempt + optional warning), body 4-col grid \`CHANNEL / QUEUED / STARTED / ELAPSED\` with \`<Time mode="relative">\` cells. Container \`var(--canvas-soft)\` / \`var(--radius-lg)\` / 14/16 padding, no border, no \`border-l-* border-l-(--accent)\` rail anywhere — see ADR-007 §9 and ADR-008 §3.
- **Use \`<DescriptionCard>\` for markdown bodies.** Renders through \`STREAMDOWN_SAFE_CONFIG\` (5 defenses: \`skipHtml\`, 13-element \`disallowedElements\`, URL-scheme allowlist via \`defaultUrlTransform\`, no streamdown chrome, canonical HTML overrides + \`SafeImage\` external-URL fallback). The XSS regression corpus in \`description-card.test.tsx\` is the security gate — do NOT relax it without an ADR — see ADR-007 §2.
- **Use \`<OwnerAvatar>\` for owner identity surfaces** (kanban cards, task rows, agent cards, timeline events, run cards). Background / foreground resolve via \`colorsFor(ownerKind, ownerId)\` against the tokenised \`--avatar-{agent|human|system}-N-{bg,fg}\` palette; sizes \`sm\` (20) / \`default\` (24) / \`lg\` (32); 2-character monogram by default with optional \`glyph\` slot. Aria-label is auto-emitted as \`"{Role} {Name}"\` — see ADR-010 §6 and ADR-013 §2.
- **Motion uses exactly three named keyframes — \`dot--pulse\` (1.8 s accent-glow), \`pill-pulse\` (2.2 s currentColor), \`pulse-accent\` (2 s accent-tint).** Tailwind's generic \`animate-pulse\` is banned across \`web/src/**\` and \`packages/ui/src/**\`. Duration tokens are \`--dur\` (140 ms) + \`--dur-slow\` (200 ms) + \`--ease\`; aliases (\`--ease-in-out\` / \`--duration-fast/base/slow\` / \`--ease-out\`) are dropped — see ADR-010 §7 and ADR-010 §8.
- **Status → tone is one declarative typed dictionary at \`web/src/lib/status-tone.ts\`** (split into \`TASK_STATUS_TONE\` / \`RUN_STATUS_TONE\` / \`TASK_LANE_TONE\` per ADR-016 §3). \`in_progress\` is \`info\`, never \`accent\`; \`completed\` is \`success\`. Consumers MUST import from the dictionary — no inlined switch statements, no per-system tone maps — see ADR-010 §5 and ADR-016 §3.
- **\`<PriorityBars>\` always renders three bars (4 / 8 / 12 px tall).** Level changes color of all three bars, never bar count: \`urgent → var(--danger)\`, \`high → var(--warning)\`, \`medium → var(--fg)\`, \`low → var(--faint)\`. The \`tone\` prop is dropped — color derives from \`level\` only — see ADR-006 §4.
- **\`<QueueHealthSparkline>\` consumes \`recharts\` via the \`@agh/ui\` adapter.** Default bar fill \`var(--bar-fill)\`; cells with \`stuck: true\` switch to \`var(--accent-tint-strong)\`. Tooltip chrome resolves through \`var(--canvas-soft)\` / \`var(--line)\` / \`var(--fg-strong)\`; never paint solid \`var(--accent)\` on a bar — see ADR-010 §3 and ADR-016 §7.
- **\`<StatusDot>\` ships 4 tones (\`warning | danger | accent | faint\`) × 2 modes (\`solid | ring\`) × 2 sizes (6 / 5 px).** Defaults to \`aria-hidden="true"\` unless a \`label\` prop is provided — see ADR-009 §5.
- **\`<Time>\` is the canonical timestamp primitive** (30 s tick refresh, accepts \`mode: "relative" | "absolute"\`, emits \`<time dateTime title>\`). Helpers (\`formatRelativeTime\` / \`formatAbsoluteTime\` / \`formatDuration\` / \`FORMAT_TIME_FALLBACK\`) live in \`@agh/ui\` at \`packages/ui/src/lib/format-time.ts\`; \`web/src/lib/format-time.ts\` is a thin re-export shim — never duplicate the implementation — see ADR-007 §3 and ADR-016 §10.
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`font-mono uppercase tracking-mono\` (or \`tracking-[Nem]\`) inline tuple.** That combination IS the \`<Eyebrow>\` contract; reinventing it skips the primitive and the \`--text-eyebrow\` / \`--tracking-mono\` tokens. Flagged by \`compozy-design-system/no-inline-eyebrow\` + \`no-inline-design-tuples\` — see ADR-016 §5 and DESIGN.md §11 "Eyebrow misuse".
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`text-[22px] font-medium tracking-[-0.026em]\` page-h1 tuple inline.** The 22 px tier no longer exists in the runtime — page identity lives in \`<Topbar>\`, detail surfaces use \`<DetailHeader>\` (24 px). Flagged by \`compozy-design-system/no-inline-design-tuples\` — see ADR-003 §2 and DESIGN.md §11 "Section as page-head".
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`border-l-* border-l-(--accent)\` / \`border-l-accent\` on cards or rows.** Active surfaces use the \`var(--fg-strong)\` indicator rail. Flagged by \`compozy-design-system/no-side-stripe-accent\` — see ADR-003 §3 and DESIGN.md §11 "Side-stripe accent rail".
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`hover:border-(--accent)\` / \`hover:bg-(--accent)\` / \`hover:text-(--accent)\`.** Hover changes background tint via \`--hover\` / \`--row-hover\` — never border / text color. Accent is the resting active/CTA state only — see ADR-004 §1, ADR-016 §5, and DESIGN.md §10 "Don't trigger accent on hover".
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`bg-[rgba(255,255,255,0.0NN)]\` literals.** Resolve through \`--row-hover\` / \`--row-selected\` / \`--surface-glaze\` / \`--bar-fill\` / \`--input-fill\` / \`--btn-default-fill\` / \`--btn-default-hover\` / \`--badge-fill\`. Flagged by \`compozy-design-system/no-design-glaze-rgba\` — see ADR-001 §6 and DESIGN.md §10 "Don't inline glaze rgba literals".
- **Anti-pattern (compile-fail): \`import { Loader2 } from "lucide-react"\` under \`web/src/routes/**\`.** Use \`<Spinner>\` for "this surface is loading data" and \`.dot--pulse\` for "this entity is in an active running state". Flagged by \`compozy-design-system/no-banned-imports\` — see ADR-009 §5, ADR-010 §8, and DESIGN.md §10 "Don't import Loader2".
- **Anti-pattern (review fail): \`<Pill tone="accent">\` co-located with \`<Button variant="primary">\` in the same toolbar / topbar / surface.** Accent budget is one target per viewport — promote the CTA, demote the pill (default neutral or \`--badge-fill\` chip). Caught at PR review by combined class-list snapshots on toolbar regions — see ADR-001 §10 and DESIGN.md §11 "Accent overload".

"
`;
